+    # Funding P&L: only paid when in position.
+    # P31 look-ahead audit (Phase B, 2026-06-22): the previous formulation
+    # `position * funding * capital` introduced a same-bar look-ahead bias —
+    # position[t] is generated by strategies/funding_capture.py from a
+    # right-aligned `rolling().mean()` of funding (line 53), so position[t]
+    # depends on funding[t]. Multiplying them at the same index lets the
+    # backtest "see" the funding rate it used to decide to be in the trade,
+    # which is impossible in live execution.
+    # Canonical fix mirrors backtest/directional_engine.py:47 (`position.shift(1) * return`):
+    # apply `funding.shift(1)` so PnL at bar t reflects the funding rate
+    # observed BEFORE the position decision at t.
+    funding_pnl = position * funding.shift(1).fillna(0) * capital
 
     # Detect transitions (entries and exits)
     pos_diff = position.diff().fillna(position.iloc[0])  # +1 = entry, -1 = exit
